Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.80,0:00:04.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter what, I'll always be your partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.85,0:00:07.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The missing final page of a book and a missing stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.12,0:00:08.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where will our deductions lead?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.99,0:00:10.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.59,0:00:12.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.31,0:00:14.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.47,0:02:07.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Man, how many years has it been\Nsince I've had to write a book report?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.85,0:02:09.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.35,0:02:10.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you even trying?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.77,0:02:13.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.14,0:02:14.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you "uh, yeah" me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.77,0:02:17.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haibara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} went home ages ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.90,0:02:21.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} and Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} are both taking this very seriously!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.78,0:02:24.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can see how Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} would be working hard, but Genta?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.74,0:02:26.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.41,0:02:29.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, you're the only one who isn't making an effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.00,0:02:32.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, even Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} is...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.71,0:02:36.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This looks so yummy!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.46,0:02:39.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uhm, Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.67,0:02:41.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.22,0:02:43.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.01,0:02:44.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This book's the one for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.43,0:02:46.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.85,0:02:49.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure you know what "book report" really means?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.02,0:02:51.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.98,0:02:52.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.73,0:02:54.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.19,0:02:56.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.98,0:03:02.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.40,0:03:03.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.11,0:03:07.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it just a prank by somebody?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.74,0:03:09.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would they do this...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.34,0:03:11.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just choose another book.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.16,0:03:12.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.29,0:03:14.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This has to be the book!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.93,0:03:16.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But still...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.08,0:03:17.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.46,0:03:20.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll help me look around, won't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.96,0:03:22.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found a clue.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.38,0:03:26.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe if we ask this kid, we'll find out something.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.43,0:03:32.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have to go too?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.68,0:03:36.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's just no excuse for tearing a page out of a school library book.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.73,0:03:39.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here we go again.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.34,0:03:46.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The missing page.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.86,0:03:50.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What does it matter?\NIt looks yummy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.37,0:03:53.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like I've told you, and more than once.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.95,0:03:55.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you listening, Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.25,0:03:57.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A book report means that...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.38,0:03:59.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.05,0:04:02.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.46,0:04:06.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hold it, buddy!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.09,0:04:08.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you all right, Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.01,0:04:11.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a rude person!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.30,0:04:13.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knocks someone down and doesn't apologize?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.93,0:04:15.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've never seen him around here before.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.52,0:04:16.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me neither.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.73,0:04:19.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's going on over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.69,0:04:23.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's check it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.15,0:04:29.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder which one he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.07,0:04:32.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's probably already gone home.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.81,0:04:35.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there a Naitou Tsukasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.62,0:04:38.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsukasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} is absent today.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.33,0:04:40.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's nothing we can do about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.92,0:04:42.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's head home, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.81,0:04:46.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He didn't call in sick or anything, so Sensei was worried about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.16,0:04:50.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No one from his house called the school?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.34,0:04:51.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.93,0:04:55.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsukasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} just transferred here in the fall, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.04,0:04:56.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.43,0:04:59.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought that he'd been looking kinda down recently...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.93,0:05:02.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder if something happened to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.29,0:05:06.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does it have something to do with this book?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.78,0:05:08.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the book!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.86,0:05:09.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.95,0:05:12.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsukasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} told me about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.91,0:05:14.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He did?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.66,0:05:17.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though school was over, he was still reading it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.62,0:05:19.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I got curious and asked him...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.19,0:05:21.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"What kind of story is that?"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.67,0:05:23.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's about Alec...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.96,0:05:28.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, Alec's the main character of the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.05,0:05:32.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One day, he loses this important harmonica.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.09,0:05:34.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he goes to ask a wise turtle what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.83,0:05:40.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The turtle says that if he can find the "Again Stone,"\Nsomething that's been lost will return to him again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.77,0:05:45.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To find the stone, he needs both a kind heart and courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.32,0:05:48.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Alec keeps searching until he finally finds the stone
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.65,0:05:54.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when Alec flashes the stone at the sky, the\Nharmonica he lost comes floating down to him!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.91,0:05:59.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I said, "If only there were a stone like that in real life."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.45,0:06:02.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Tsukasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} laughed a little and said, "Yeah."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.83,0:06:05.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, let's go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.13,0:06:07.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go where?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.53,0:06:08.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where else?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.96,0:06:10.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To Tsukasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s house, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.59,0:06:14.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, excuse us!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.30,0:06:16.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there a case?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.01,0:06:18.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I really doubt that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.43,0:06:20.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.85,0:06:23.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A precious stone that was on display in that room got stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.13,0:06:26.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Mitsuhiko...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.57,0:06:27.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That man just now...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.36,0:06:30.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you get it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.11,0:06:32.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's the stone thief!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.74,0:06:34.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.36,0:06:36.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why he ran away like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.53,0:06:40.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, it's time for the Detective Boys to get to work!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.04,0:06:41.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.87,0:06:42.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.37,0:06:45.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.25,0:06:49.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since she drew us a map, we'll find it in no time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.67,0:06:50.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.30,0:06:54.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Kobayashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.42,0:06:56.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.09,0:06:58.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, something troublesome happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.43,0:06:59.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Troublesome?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.93,0:07:02.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the truth is...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.77,0:07:07.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I borrowed a stone sample from Beika Museum for a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.56,0:07:09.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And now it's been stolen!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.94,0:07:11.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a really valuable stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.36,0:07:15.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I promised to return it later today.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.36,0:07:16.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sensei...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.89,0:07:19.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,May we take a look around the science room?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.21,0:07:26.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know it was here after class yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.00,0:07:29.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They were pretty reckless.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.23,0:07:32.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's hard to think of this as the work of a professional.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.30,0:07:38.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Returnolith"?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.83,0:07:39.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, we just...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.68,0:07:42.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, can you show me that book again?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.17,0:07:45.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.98,0:07:47.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.73,0:07:50.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm pretty sure a stone was mentioned here, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.73,0:07:55.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Again Stone and the Returnolith...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.16,0:08:03.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.58,0:08:07.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's possible that the person who stole the stone also read this book.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.50,0:08:11.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsukasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} returned this book yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.96,0:08:16.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The stone was taken sometime between\Nyesterday after school and today.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.55,0:08:19.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.97,0:08:21.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.33,0:08:22.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lets go, Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.97,0:08:24.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To look for the stone thief?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.93,0:08:27.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To Tsukasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s house.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.19,0:08:33.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm starving...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.80,0:08:36.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've completely lost sight of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.19,0:08:38.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was just in front of us a second ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.95,0:08:39.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.60,0:08:43.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There he is, the stone thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.12,0:08:44.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go, Mitsuhiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.16,0:08:45.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.17,0:08:54.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We lost him again!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.38,0:08:57.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I'm almost certain he went this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.60,0:09:04.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe this is the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.22,0:09:05.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.73,0:09:07.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.03,0:09:16.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you kids want?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.11,0:09:18.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.24,0:09:20.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please spare our lives!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.24,0:09:23.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you think Tsukasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was the one who took the stone?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.33,0:09:28.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Tsukasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was the one who ripped out the page,\Nit's highly possible that he took the stone, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.58,0:09:30.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's true, then Tsukasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s a bad kid, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.94,0:09:33.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I told you, we don't know that just yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.25,0:09:35.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.47,0:09:44.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse us!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.81,0:09:53.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What're you two doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.15,0:09:56.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.44,0:09:58.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're hungry, there's plenty more to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.03,0:10:07.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mister...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.33,0:10:14.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You heard from Tsukasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s teacher that he\Nnever showed up for class today, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.75,0:10:18.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have any idea where he could have gone?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.76,0:10:23.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't you worried about Tsukasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.76,0:10:25.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I am, but I'm still gonna eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.79,0:10:33.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true that we came here on a misunderstanding,\Nand ended up eating some exquisite food, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.81,0:10:36.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that we've heard what's happened, it changes everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.23,0:10:40.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, I'm busy getting the restaurant ready to open.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.47,0:10:42.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't your wife help?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.44,0:10:44.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's none of your business!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.32,0:10:45.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, mister.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.49,0:10:48.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could you show us Tsukasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s room?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.12,0:10:50.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We might learn something new.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.33,0:10:52.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you wanna do that for?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.41,0:10:54.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because we're worried about Tsukasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.51,0:11:07.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you doing, Tsukasa?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.79,0:11:10.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.35,0:11:13.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Boys like you ought to be playing\Nsoccer with their friends or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.48,0:11:19.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't have any friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.53,0:11:27.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you kids are Tsukasa's...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.81,0:11:30.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're his friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.67,0:11:36.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If my deductions are correct...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.00,0:11:40.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After Tsukasa read that book, he found\Nthe stone in the science room.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.88,0:11:44.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He then became convinced that it was the\N"Again Stone" mentioned in the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.88,0:11:48.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then this morning he came to school,\Ntook the stone, and disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.26,0:11:50.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what's his motive?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.10,0:11:54.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is Tsukasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} trying to get back?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.71,0:11:56.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.23,0:11:59.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About this, could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.48,0:12:05.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsukasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.03,0:12:08.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So she passed away...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.52,0:12:13.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She looks so kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.91,0:12:16.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But now she's gone...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.13,0:12:25.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.10,0:12:36.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How'd it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.14,0:12:42.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His dad doesn't know what beach it is, but it appears\Nto be a secret spot shared between him and his mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.32,0:12:43.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.65,0:12:46.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could this beach be where Tsukasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} is now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.36,0:12:47.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We still can't know for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.82,0:12:49.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.20,0:12:50.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You find something?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.63,0:12:52.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All kinds of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.79,0:13:00.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, bring the book over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.63,0:13:04.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Flip to the page that's torn.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.07,0:13:05.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.63,0:13:09.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.64,0:13:14.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsukasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s definitely the one who tore the page out of the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.64,0:13:19.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He brought the page home with him,\Nand cut off the edge he didn't need.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.14,0:13:23.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means, we can look at Tsukasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}\Nas the person who took the stone, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.23,0:13:24.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.05,0:13:25.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Great work, Genta!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.69,0:13:29.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The stopper on the back is loose.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.99,0:13:31.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see what's inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.28,0:13:35.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's some kind of note.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.77,0:13:38.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With some strange words.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.08,0:13:39.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What does it say?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.29,0:13:41.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Crab{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is scissors scissors...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.04,0:13:42.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The orange is paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.25,0:13:43.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The caterpillar is rock...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.79,0:13:45.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Paper scissors.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.28,0:13:46.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you think it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.53,0:13:50.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sounds like a code to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.05,0:13:51.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure does.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.16,0:13:53.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, you need to be thinking, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.93,0:13:56.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This could be a clue!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.04,0:13:57.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Crab{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, scissors scissors...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.81,0:13:59.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What could it mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.46,0:14:02.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it, Mitsuhiko?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.10,0:14:03.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, stay just like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.94,0:14:05.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please don't move.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.65,0:14:08.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I should stay just like... this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.15,0:14:12.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Crab{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, scissors scissors.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.16,0:14:14.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I figured it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.41,0:14:16.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know what that code means!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.91,0:14:21.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That sea is supposed to be a secret place\Nfor Tsukasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and his mom, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.25,0:14:24.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And behind their picture was the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.14,0:14:28.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This code is like a map, which means it tells us how to get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.92,0:14:30.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, Mitsuhiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.97,0:14:33.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means, which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.34,0:14:34.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.33,0:14:38.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They rode a crab to get there?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.13,0:14:39.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.27,0:14:41.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Crabs are red, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.02,0:14:44.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that stands for the TR Touto Line.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.15,0:14:45.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Keep going.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.44,0:14:47.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Scissors scissors" means four fingers are up.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.44,0:14:49.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that means...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.15,0:14:50.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stations...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.32,0:14:52.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And maybe that equals the number of stations!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.82,0:14:53.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.44,0:14:54.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now what do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.70,0:14:56.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's get going before it gets dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.23,0:15:03.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Four stops away from Beika Station on the Touto Line...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.00,0:15:07.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, that could work for either inbound or outbound.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.67,0:15:09.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next, it's the "orange" part.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.63,0:15:10.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Orange-colored!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.55,0:15:14.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the Sakaimachi and Minato Lines are both orange.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.87,0:15:18.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, why is Crab{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} the only one with the honorific "-san"?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.26,0:15:19.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because he's more important?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.85,0:15:21.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Platform 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.52,0:15:23.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,1 & 2 are for limited-express trains.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.21,0:15:24.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And which way is Platform 3 for?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.15,0:15:25.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inbound, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.23,0:15:26.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.23,0:15:32.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the next station, we transfer to the Minato Line...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.11,0:15:34.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then we'll get off five stops later because\Nof the five fingers in "paper".
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.53,0:15:36.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The problem is, what do we do from there?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.57,0:15:37.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.25,0:15:46.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.46,0:15:48.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes—right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.11,0:15:49.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.65,0:16:14.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're back!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.20,0:16:18.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We had so much fun, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.03,0:16:19.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.66,0:16:23.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Mom was so funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.37,0:16:25.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the waves rushed up, she—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.37,0:16:27.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I told you to always come in through the back door!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.89,0:16:29.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.92,0:16:31.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here, it's a souvenir
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.96,0:16:34.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next time, come with us, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.92,0:16:51.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're in trouble, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.19,0:16:54.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no other train that we can transfer to from this station.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.82,0:16:56.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rock means zero, I'm sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.61,0:16:59.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there's no such thing as a Platform 0 for a train.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.18,0:17:00.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.82,0:17:03.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what does the caterpillar stand for?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.18,0:17:07.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The bus terminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.21,0:17:10.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a Bus Number 0!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.46,0:17:12.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Try thinking of the caterpillar as a bus instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.42,0:17:14.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.54,0:17:15.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.34,0:17:18.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it wasn't a real caterpillar... wait up!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.35,0:17:23.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't that look like a caterpillar?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.14,0:17:24.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This has to be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.68,0:17:26.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll go ask the bus driver.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.02,0:17:29.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, are you really sure, Conan?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.52,0:17:32.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Tsukasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s not there...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.06,0:17:33.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.34,0:17:35.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How'd it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.54,0:17:37.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.23,0:17:42.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Paper scissors" makes seven, and the seventh\Nstop from that bus is indeed Ohama Beach!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.41,0:17:44.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That settles it, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.29,0:17:55.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsukasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} has to be at that beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.30,0:17:59.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's the sea!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.97,0:18:01.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Great, just a little further.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.89,0:18:11.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sea, the sea!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.06,0:18:13.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We didn't come here to play, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.44,0:18:15.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's split up and search.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.31,0:18:16.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you find him, contact us immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.90,0:18:17.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.65,0:18:19.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's get going too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.16,0:18:29.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.28,0:18:30.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please let us find him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.72,0:18:47.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsukasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.39,0:18:49.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So we finally made it...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.29,0:18:50.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To the last page.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.67,0:18:53.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsukasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.10,0:18:55.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Naitou Tsukasa kun from 1st grade, class A, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.01,0:18:59.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who are you two?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.28,0:19:02.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We both go to Teitan Elementary, and I'm Edogawa Conan.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.32,0:19:05.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My name is Yoshida Ayumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.57,0:19:06.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The truth is..
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.10,0:19:07.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, the sea, the sea!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.74,0:19:10.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So this is where you were, Tsukasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.83,0:19:14.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's have some fun since we're at the beach!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.29,0:19:15.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.33,0:19:16.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You, too, Tsukasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.21,0:19:18.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on, come on—it'll be great.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.73,0:19:22.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, sumo.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.05,0:19:23.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's do sumo!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.20,0:19:26.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're not gonna get me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.81,0:19:31.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's fired up!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.23,0:19:32.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bring it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.22,0:19:36.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsukasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} sure looks like he's having fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.84,0:19:37.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.23,0:19:41.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, how did you know he'd be here?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.36,0:19:45.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because the sea in that photo looked just like the one in the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.03,0:19:47.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's all?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.09,0:19:51.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There had to be a reason he tore the page\Nout of the book and took the stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.12,0:19:56.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something Tsukasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} wanted to get back\Neven if he had to break the rules to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.63,0:19:57.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that is...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.57,0:19:59.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.88,0:20:00.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.53,0:20:06.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsukasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} wanted to use the stone's\Npower to bring his deceased mother back.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.91,0:20:10.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the rest was all thanks to Mitsuhiko's deduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.43,0:20:12.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.29,0:20:13.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsukasa!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.77,0:20:18.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.23,0:20:21.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about the restaurant?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.19,0:20:22.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.97,0:20:24.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.22,0:20:25.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How'd you know where I was?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.28,0:20:28.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This led me here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.49,0:20:35.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.37,0:20:39.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought if I came here, I'd be able to see Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.27,0:20:56.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.30,0:21:03.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsukasa...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.83,0:21:18.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It took so long to get here, I'm hungry all over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.79,0:21:21.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mister, feed us some more yakitori!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.36,0:21:23.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No more, Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.33,0:21:24.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.46,0:21:26.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Keep taking care of Tsukasa for me, all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.49,0:21:29.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You got it, just leave it to us!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.97,0:23:00.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you found the stone, Naitou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.31,0:23:03.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sensei, uhm...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.31,0:23:04.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.83,0:23:08.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We looked for it, too, but didn't have any luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.53,0:23:19.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sensei, I'm the one who took the stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.87,0:23:25.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm glad that you're being honest with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.79,0:23:28.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you can't do things like that any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.63,0:23:32.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.68,0:23:38.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sensei, check out my homework!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.51,0:23:40.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, you sure finished up quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.06,0:23:43.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is your report?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.52,0:23:46.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks yummy, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.13,0:23:48.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on, Genta kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.09,0:23:50.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The assignment was to write a book report.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.48,0:23:53.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That looks more like a picture diary!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.43,0:23:55.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's so like you, Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.03,0:23:58.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, is eating the only thing ever on your mind?
